# Product Video Smart Crop

For Qwertystock product pages, video assets must not use a single poster frame
as the final smart-crop signal.

- Video smart crop should analyze 15 preview frames extracted with ffmpeg from
  the product preview video.
- The crop target is the alternate aspect ratio: horizontal source gets a
  vertical crop, vertical source gets a horizontal crop.
- Detectron results should be used to identify one main subject instance across
  the frame sequence, not a changing union of unrelated objects.
- Missing detections between valid frames should be interpolated.
- Main subject bounding boxes and resulting crop windows should be smoothed so
  the preview does not jitter.
- Keep the product page fallback safe: if video frame extraction or Detectron
  fails, fall back to the static thumbnail center/smart crop instead of breaking
  the product page.
- Do not send full mask arrays for all video frames to the browser unless there
  is a specific UI need. Video smart crop should prefer compact boxes and a
  tracked main subject to keep page payload small.

When changing this flow, test a video product page such as
`https://qwertystock.com/item?id=3294455` and verify the smart-crop panel reaches
ready/fallback state without blocking purchase/download controls.
